On Downloads, why does it say "NetOffice 1.7.3 Oct 10, 2016, updated Oct 11" ?
I downloaded, but it is still the version from March 2015.

I've been just added the current source state to the downloads because some people ask for.
(microsoft stop any maintenance for codeplex and the SVN bridge is still broken)
It looks like codeplex update the release date here automaticaly - sorry for that.

*Sebastian

Hi,

Someone could confirm if this current version is compatible with Excel 2016 ..?

Thanks

true. Office 2016 is the same as its previous version because Microsoft left off the COM API.
The good news: This means to have more space for agressive optimizations in NetOffice. No need to take care for the future anymore.

*Sebastian
